
This directory contains project-specific libraries for the ClockDevice firmware.
Each library is placed in its own subdirectory and compiled by PlatformIO as a
static library linked into the final firmware binary.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Directory structure
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

lib/
 ├── buttons/          Button state-machine (single / double / triple click, hold)
 │   ├── buttons.h
 │   └── buttons.c
 │
 ├── buzzer/           Passive-buzzer driver via ESP32 LEDC (tones + melodies)
 │   ├── buzzer.h
 │   └── buzzer.c
 │
 ├── clock_ui/         UI state-machine (normal clock view + all settings modes)
 │   ├── clock_ui.h
 │   └── clock_ui.c
 │
 ├── ds1302/           Bit-banged driver for the DS1302 RTC module
 │   ├── ds1302.h
 │   └── ds1302.c
 │
 ├── led_ring/         WS2812B 12-LED ring driver via IDF led_strip component
 │   ├── led_ring.h
 │   └── led_ring.c
 │
 └── tm1637/           Bit-banged driver for the TM1637 4-digit 7-segment display
     ├── tm1637.h
     └── tm1637.c

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dependency diagram
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 main.c
   ├── ds1302      (RTC read/write)
   ├── tm1637      (display output)
   ├── buzzer      (sound output)
   ├── led_ring    (LED ring output — depends on espressif/led_strip IDF component)
   ├── buttons     (user input)
   └── clock_ui    (orchestrates tm1637 + led_ring + buzzer + ds1302 for settings UI)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IDF component dependency
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

led_ring uses the espressif/led_strip IDF component declared in src/idf_component.yml.
No extra lib_deps entries in platformio.ini are required.

More information about PlatformIO Library Dependency Finder:
https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/ldf.html


For example, see the structure of the following example libraries `Foo` and `Bar`:

|--lib
|  |
|  |--Bar
|  |  |--docs
|  |  |--examples
|  |  |--src
|  |     |- Bar.c
|  |     |- Bar.h
|  |  |- library.json (optional. for custom build options, etc) https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/config.html
|  |
|  |--Foo
|  |  |- Foo.c
|  |  |- Foo.h
|  |
|  |- README --> THIS FILE
|
|- platformio.ini
|--src
   |- main.c

Example contents of `src/main.c` using Foo and Bar:
```
#include <Foo.h>
#include <Bar.h>

int main (void)
{
  ...
}

```

The PlatformIO Library Dependency Finder will find automatically dependent
libraries by scanning project source files.

More information about PlatformIO Library Dependency Finder
- https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/ldf.html
